CatDescriptText: Lois Grimball, McKeesport, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 17, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you believe that city patrolmen and firemen should be required to work more than 40 hours per week?" answer reads: "No, if there is no overtime pay allotted. However, everybody who works overtime should receive a few more dollars."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Lois Grimball wearing dark shirt and belt, plaid skirt, and light colored cardigan sweater with clipped beaded chain with "D" charm, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
